<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec9>

Streptococcus suis in the People's Republic of China
-----------------------------------------------
Immediate notification report
Information received on 5 Aug 2005 from Mr. Jia Youling, Director
General, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing:
Report date: 5 Aug 2005.
Reason for immediate notification: an emerging disease with
significant morbidity or mortality, or zoonotic potential (though
this is not a disease notifiable to the OIE).
Precise identification of agent: _Streptococcus suis_ B.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 25 Jul 2005.
Date of start of the event: 25 Jun 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, post-mortem and laboratory.
Details of outbreaks:
1st administrative division (province): Sichuan
Lower administrative division (city): Chengdu
Type of epidemiological unit: ...
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Aug 2005
Species: sui
Number of animals in the outbreaks:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
19 / 15 / 1 / 19 / 0
1st administrative division (province): Sichuan
Lower administrative division (city): Deyang
Type of epidemiological unit: ...
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Jul 2005
Species: sui
Number of animals in the outbreaks:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
66 / 5 / 5 / 66 / 0
1st administrative division (province): Sichuan
Lower administrative division (city): Luzhou
Type of epidemiological unit: ...
Date of start of the outbreak: 12 Jul 2005
Species: sui
Number of animals in the outbreaks:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
7 / 2 / 2 / 7 / 0
1st administrative division (province): Sichuan
Lower administrative division (city): Mianyang
Type of epidemiological unit: ...
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Jul 2005
